column5: Hey folks I think I might have to sell my canoe. The problem is I cant lift it over my head to load it on the roof of my SUV. What does a 16 ft fiberglass go for. Its not new and it was given to me. I hate to sell it, but if i cant lift it I cant use it. What do you guys think?
Your gonna need to post some pictures of it if you want to get an idea of its worth.  Don
anywhere from $250 for a beater, or, if it's in decent shape, newer, and is a good make, maybe up to $800, fiberglass canoes aren't as attractive as kevlar, royalex etc
Might this help?  cabelos easyloader canoe   Art
start working out and keep the canoe
How about building one.I have an axle with 5 leaf springs and wheels I can sell.
No need to "sell it"... just pay it forward and give it to me   Let me know when and where to pick it up.. I can be there with very short notice.
